                     <p>Autograph motto for the poem, untitled but numbered 4. and identified
								on f. 3r as "4. Ode, to Adversity", in MS instructions to 
								<extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Dodsley, James, 1724-1797"
                                show="replace">
                           <persname normal="Dodsley, James, 1724-1797">Dodsley</persname>
                        </extref> for the <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1768"
                                show="replace">
                           <date normal="1768" type="publication">1768</date>
                           <geogname normal="London (Greater London, England, United Kingdom),            inhabited place [7011781]">London</geogname> edition</extref>, sent in a <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/display.cgi?text=tgal0521"
                                show="replace">letter</extref>, <date normal="17680201" certainty="circa">[1?] February
													1768</date>. 
								The motto first appeared in the poem's version in <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1768&amp;text=otad"
                                show="replace">
                           <title render="italic">Poems</title>
                        </extref> (<date normal="1768" type="publication">1768</date>).
							</p>
